cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving word embeddings for natural language processing systems.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a probabilistic framework for incorporating morphological information into word embeddings.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper is about improving the performance of natural language processing systems.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neural word embeddings.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any applications to computer vision, but it is still possible as word embeddings are used in various computer vision tasks.
